# Error Handling & Logging

## Error Handling Pattern
- Wrap all Chrome API calls in try-catch with typed error handling
- Use custom error classes: `SentraError`, `ClinicalError`, `ScraperError`, `StorageError`
- Never swallow errors silently — always log or re-throw
- Clinical modules: errors MUST be logged with patient-safety context

## Structured Logging
```typescript
// Required log fields for audit compliance
interface AuditLog {
  timestamp: string;     // ISO 8601
  level: 'info' | 'warn' | 'error' | 'critical';
  module: string;        // e.g., 'cdss.sepsis', 'scraper.vitals'
  action: string;        // what happened
  userId?: string;       // hashed
  context?: Record<string, unknown>;
}
```

## Log Levels
- `info`: normal operations (feature used, data fetched)
- `warn`: recoverable issues (retry succeeded, fallback used)
- `error`: operation failed (API error, parse failure)
- `critical`: patient-safety relevant (CDSS failure, data corruption)

## Forbidden
- No `console.log` in production — use structured logger
- No PII (patient names, IDs) in logs — hash or omit
- No stack traces exposed to end users
- No `catch(e) {}` empty catch blocks

## Retention
- Extension local logs: 30-day rolling window
- Critical logs: flag for export to audit system
